early_life_description: Born in London, Elizabeth became heir presumptive after her uncle's abdication in 1936.
young_adult_description: Served in the Auxiliary Territorial Service during World War II.
adult_life_description: Became Queen in 1952 and reigned for 70 years, overseeing a period of great social change.
late_life_description: Remained dedicated to her duties until her passing in 2022.

early_life_description: Born into the Scottish aristocracy as the ninth of ten children.
young_adult_description: Married Prince Albert (later King George VI) in 1923.
adult_life_description: Became a symbol of national resilience during WWII.
late_life_description: Lived to 101, beloved by the public as the Queen Mother.

early_life_description: Second son of King George V and Queen Mary.
young_adult_description: Served in the Royal Navy during WWI.
adult_life_description: Became King in 1936 after his brother's abdication; led Britain through WWII.
late_life_description: Died in 1952, succeeded by his daughter Elizabeth II.

early_life_description: Grandson of Queen Victoria, born into the royal family.
young_adult_description: Served in the Royal Navy before becoming heir apparent.
adult_life_description: Renamed the royal house to Windsor in 1917 during WWI.
late_life_description: Died in 1936, succeeded by his son Edward VIII.

early_life_description: Born Princess Victoria Mary of Teck.
adult_life_description: Served as Queen Consort and later Queen Mother to George VI.
late_life_description: Known for dignity and strong sense of duty.

early_life_description: Born Prince Philip of Greece and Denmark.
young_adult_description: Served in the Royal Navy during WWII.
adult_life_description: Married Queen Elizabeth II in 1947 and supported her throughout her reign.
late_life_description: Retired from royal duties in 2017 and passed away in 2021.

early_life_description: First child of Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Philip.
young_adult_description: Served in the Royal Navy and became Prince of Wales in 1958.
adult_life_description: Known for environmental and charitable work through The Prince’s Trust.
late_life_description: Became King in 2022 following his mother’s death.

early_life_description: Born into the Spencer family, raised in British nobility.
young_adult_description: Married Prince Charles in 1981 in a globally televised ceremony.
adult_life_description: Beloved for her humanitarian work and compassion.
late_life_description: Died tragically in 1997; remembered as the 'People’s Princess'.

early_life_description: Second child and only daughter of Queen Elizabeth II.
young_adult_description: Represented the monarchy worldwide; accomplished equestrian.

early_life_description: Third child of Queen Elizabeth II.
young_adult_description: Served in the Royal Navy during the Falklands War.
adult_life_description: Married Sarah Ferguson; father of Beatrice and Eugenie.

early_life_description: Youngest child of Queen Elizabeth II.
young_adult_description: Worked in arts and public service.
adult_life_description: Became Duke of Edinburgh after his father’s death.

early_life_description: Eldest son of Charles and Diana.
young_adult_description: Served in the RAF and became active in charity work.
adult_life_description: Married Catherine Middleton in 2011; heir apparent to the throne.

early_life_description: Younger son of Charles and Diana.
young_adult_description: Served in the British Army and founded the Invictus Games.
adult_life_description: Married Meghan Markle in 2018 and stepped back from senior royal duties in 2020.
